body:
# Claude Code Hook Presets

Six hooks you can copy into your `~/.claude/settings.json` or a plugin's `hooks/` directory. Every one is written per the RuleSell hook safety rules:

1. Always wrap with `timeout Ns`
2. Always exit 0 on uncertainty
3. Never block by default
4. Never read outside the project root
5. Idempotent — safe to run on every matching event

## 1. Format on save

```json
{
  "PostToolUse": [
    {
      "matcher": "Edit|Write",
      "hooks": [
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "timeout 10s npx prettier --write \"$CLAUDE_FILE_PATH\" 2>/dev/null || exit 0"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

## 2. Lint after write

```json
{
  "PostToolUse": [
    {
      "matcher": "Edit|Write",
      "hooks": [
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "timeout 15s npx eslint --fix \"$CLAUDE_FILE_PATH\" 2>&1 | head -20 || exit 0"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

Note: we pipe to `head -20` so even a linter that emits thousands of errors can't spam the terminal.

## 3. Run tests on edit (debounced via lock file)

```json
{
  "PostToolUse": [
    {
      "matcher": "Edit|Write",
      "hooks": [
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "mkdir -p /tmp/claude-locks && [ ! -f /tmp/claude-locks/test-running ] && (touch /tmp/claude-locks/test-running; timeout 90s npm test 2>&1 | tail -20; rm -f /tmp/claude-locks/test-running) || exit 0"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

This one uses a lock file to prevent concurrent runs. Without the lock, Claude can easily fire 10 test runs in parallel during a multi-file refactor.

## 4. Block commits with secrets (PreToolUse)

```json
{
  "PreToolUse": [
    {
      "matcher": "Bash",
      "hooks": [
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "case \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_INPUT\" in *'git commit'*|*'git add'*) timeout 5s git diff --cached | grep -Ei 'sk-(live|test)_|api_key|password\\s*=|BEGIN.*PRIVATE KEY' && (echo '❌ Potential secret in staged changes — commit blocked.' >&2; exit 2) || exit 0 ;; esac; exit 0"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

Exit code 2 blocks the tool call. Use sparingly — blocking is the nuclear option.

## 5. Screenshot after UI file edit

```json
{
  "PostToolUse": [
    {
      "matcher": "Edit|Write",
      "hooks": [
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "case \"$CLAUDE_FILE_PATH\" in *.tsx|*.jsx|*.vue|*.svelte) mkdir -p .claude-screenshots && timeout 20s curl -s http://localhost:3000 > /dev/null && echo 'ℹ Dev server up — run /screenshot to capture.' ;; esac; exit 0"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

Rather than actually taking a screenshot (which requires a headless browser setup), this one nudges the agent to use the existing screenshot tool.

## 6. Rate-limit bash commands (fail on too many per minute)

```json
{
  "PreToolUse": [
    {
      "matcher": "Bash",
      "hooks": [
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "mkdir -p /tmp/claude-rate && N=$(ls /tmp/claude-rate/ts-* 2>/dev/null | wc -l) && [ \"$N\" -lt 30 ] && touch \"/tmp/claude-rate/ts-$(date +%s)\" && find /tmp/claude-rate/ -name 'ts-*' -mmin +1 -delete && exit 0 || (echo '❌ Too many bash calls in the last minute — cooling off.' >&2; exit 2)"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

## Combining hooks

All six can live in a single `settings.json`. They're keyed by event type, so Claude Code runs them in order for matching tools. Mix and match.

## Debugging hooks

- Run Claude Code with `--debug` to see hook execution logs
- Every hook logs stderr by default — check `~/.claude/logs/`
- If a hook appears not to fire, check the matcher regex against the tool name
- If a hook blocks every command, you probably forgot `|| exit 0`

